LAGOS – Telecommunications services provider, Airtel Nigeria, has announced the elevation of Adebimpe Ayo Elias as Director, Human Resources & Administration, with effect from 1st July 2022. In her new role, Ms. Ayo-Elias will be responsible for driving Airtel Nigeria’s people agenda with a keen focus on ensuring an inspired, happy, and highly engaged workforce. Prior to this elevation, Ms. Ayo-Elias held the position of Head, HR Business Partnering and she brings on board 25+ years of cognate experience garnered across several industries including telecommunications, software and fintech, and human resource consulting. Airtel Nigeria unveils commercial data centre to support businesses, organisations, earns N304 billion revenue from data services Surendran Chemmenkotil, Managing Director & Chief Executive Officer, Airtel Nigeria, while commenting on the occasion, said: “Airtel is committed to growing and empowering its internal talent pool as well as reinforcing its drive towards gender diversity, at every level starting with leadership. “At Airtel, our employees are our competitive advantage, and we are committed to creating opportunities for all our talented people to succeed, grow, achieve their full potential and fulfil their personal and professional aspirations. “Adebimpe Ayo Elias has proven to be a transformational leader who is passionate about people, and we are very confident that she will deliver on our people agenda as we position as employer of first choice for talented Nigerians,” he added.